
[1]broth

   BROTH, n. brauth.

   1. Liquor in which flesh is boiled and macerated,usually with rice and
   herbs, or some ingredient to give it a better relish.

   2. In America, the word is often applied to foaming water, and
   especially to a mixture of snow and water in the highways which is
   called snow-broth.
